The '''Wizard of Yendor''' (also informally known as "[[Rodney]]"), {{monsym|Wizard of Yendor}}, is a [[unique]] [[monster]] that serves as one of the main antagonists of ''[[NetHack]]''. He is a powerful [[Human (monster attribute)|human]] sorcerer that is a [[M2_PRINCE|prince]] to his kind.

The Wizard of Yendor is the guardian of the [[Book of the Dead]], and the [[hero]] must retrieve it in order to perform the [[Invocation]], gain access to [[Moloch's Sanctum]] and take the [[Amulet of Yendor]] from the [[high priest]] of [[Moloch]]. However, killing him alone will not be enough to deter him: the Wizard can not only [[#Harassment|harass heroes remotely]] with mysterious curses and spells, but will eventually reappear stronger than ever. He will even follow the [[hero]] to the [[Elemental Planes]], with a guaranteed reappearance on the [[Plane of Earth]] unless he has been [[#Driving off the Wizard|made to flee the dungeon]].

[[Eating]] the Wizard of Yendor's [[corpse]] or [[tin]] will grant [[fire resistance]], [[poison resistance]], [[teleportitis]], or [[teleport control]], with an equal chance of each.

==Generation==
The Wizard of Yendor is always generated hostile, will not appear in a [[bones]] level and is not a valid form for [[polymorph]].

residing within [[Wizard's Tower|his Tower]] in [[Gehennom]], with the Book of the Dead placed on his square. When generated on the Plane of Earth, he is [[Monster starting inventory|always created with]] a [[spellbook of dig]].{{refsrc|src/makemon.c|1301|nethack=3.6.7}}

==Abilities==
The Wizard of Yendor has -8 [[AC]] and full [[Magic resistance (monster)|monster magic resistance]], along with fire resistance and poison resistance; he is [[breathless]], [[regenerate]]s, can [[see invisible]], can be seen via [[infravision]], and is capable of [[flight]]. The Wizard is [[covetous]] and can warp to the hero's position, and also has a form of teleport control: [[teleport]]ing him will always move him to the upstairs of that floor, and if he is teleported inside his Tower, he will always end up on the down [[ladder]].{{refsrc|src/teleport.c|1239|nethack=3.6.7}}

The Wizard of Yendor has a strong 'claw' attack that has a {{frac|20}} chance of stealing the Amulet of Yendor, any [[invocation items]] or any [[quest artifact]]s the hero possesses, and will attempt to cast one mage [[monster spell]] per turn of combat: he has access to the full complement of arcane [[monster spell]]s, up to and including the [[touch of death]]. As both his Amulet-stealing attack and monster spellcasting in general are only coded for player-versus-monster combat, the Wizard of Yendor is incapable of harming other monsters.<ref name="mhitu">His Amulet-stealing attack is handled entirely in mhitu.c, and mcastu.c has no provisions for monster vs. monster spellcasting.</ref>

The Wizard also has a unique mage spell known as [[Double Trouble]], which [[Division|creates another incarnation of him]] with all his powers, and he will not use this spell if there are already two of him in the world.{{refsrc|src/mcastu.c|398|nethack=3.6.7}} The clone can be created with a different appearance from his normal self, and may be any one of the following monsters: [[Human (monster)|human]], [[water demon]], [[vampire]], [[red dragon]], [[troll]], [[umber hulk]], [[xorn]], [[xan]], [[cockatrice]], [[floating eye]], [[guardian naga]], or [[trapper]].{{refsrc|src/wizard.c|49|nethack=3.6.7}}{{refsrc|src/wizard.c|497|nethack=3.6.7}} The Wizard's clone will have all the abilities of the monster he is disguised as, and attacking a disguised clone will cause him to shift to his normal form.

===Harassment===
Once the Wizard of Yendor is killed or the Invocation is performed, the game recognizes the hero as a [[demigod]]&mdash;see that article for details on its other effects. The Wizard will begin to harass the hero with negative effects, regardless of whether he is alive or present on the hero's level, and will continue to do so for the rest of the game. The timer is set to 50-299 turns after the Wizard first dies, while performing the Invocation sets it to the lowest value between the current timer and 2-12 turns, and the timer is reset to 50-249 turns after a harassment effect occurs, all of which exclude the period of [[invulnerability]] from a successful [[prayer]].{{refsrc|src/spell.c|265|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}{{refsrc|src/allmain.c|289|version=NetHack 3.6.7|comment=timer only sets and decrements if the hero is a demigod}}

When the hero is harassed, one of the following effects will happen:{{refsrc|src/wizard.c|684|nethack=3.6.7}}
